Check maximum number of session in db2:

db2 get db cfg for <dbname> | grep -i maxappls

Check Current Sessions:

db2 list applications | wc -l



In DB2 LUW, the session limit is controlled by the MAXAPPLS parameter (Maximum number of active applications). You can change it at the database level.

Steps to Set Session Limit in DB2
1. Connect to the database
db2 connect to <dbname>

2. Update MAXAPPLS
To set the session limit explicitly, run:
db2 update db cfg for <dbname> using MAXAPPLS 300


This example sets the limit to 300 concurrent sessions.

3. If you prefer automatic tuning
You can let DB2 decide dynamically:
db2 update db cfg for <dbname> using MAXAPPLS AUTOMATIC

4. Verify change
db2 get db cfg for <dbname> | grep -i maxappls

5. Restart Database (sometimes required)

In some cases, you need to stop and restart the database for the change to take effect:

db2 terminate
db2stop
db2start
